properties.name: 10th and Main
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessThis is where I got rear-ended by a Chevy. I had stopped for a red light and I guess that wasn\'t what the kid expected. I didn\'t get hurt by the bike got banged up a little. I got very good help from the local police but it still took a day off our trip with getting all the paperwork and later getting the bike fixed. Riding it to the motel was no fun, the back fender was all bent and kept hitting the wheel. We borrowed some tools from the lady at the hotel and managed to wrench it right. I was a bit wary about riding for a few days after.

properties.name: Gzira Malta
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessMalta is such a great place. Lovely people, lots of history, great diving and good food. We also found the best icecream ever and we went to the small stand every day even though the people selling it were almost hostile.

properties.name: Heiligenblut
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessWe stayed at a great hotel here. The food was fantastic and we got great service what ever we asked for. Heiligenblut is also the south gateway to the Grossglockner Hochalpenstrasse and we made the most of it. Some of the best motocycle riding anywhere! The road is well kept and the hairpins are pletifull. The views are amazing wherever you look.

properties.name: London
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessThis is just one of the many places I\'ve been in London, for a few years I couldn\'t imagine going somewhere else for my vacations. I love everything about London, and the UK and I can\'t see myself ever growing tired of it.

properties.name: Meramac Caves
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessIt\'s not hard to find this place riding the old highway 66. There must have been more than 25 signs leading up to Stanton. (It was much harder to figure out where to place the marker on the map.) Before making it this far we picked up lost frenchman and he was great company all day. He didn\'t want to go down the cave but waited for us. It\'s a great dripstone cave and with the lights it really is mystical. It\'s not an easy tour, lots of walking up and down but so worth it. The food in the restaurant was good as well. One of our first sightseeing stops on our Route 66 trip. The photo shows my boyfriend Fredrik and the two James brothers, Jessie and Frank.

properties.name: Mid point café Route 66
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessOnce you\'re in Adrian Texas you\'ve made it half way to Los Angeles and boy were we grateful. For a while I didn\'t think we\'d get out of Oklahoma, things just kept going wrong. At the cafe we got some pie and soda and our spirits were lifted equally by the food and the long chat we had with the lady running the place. When we left she helped us take the picture and last but not least gave some bumperstickers, although we saved those for our cars back home.

properties.name: Parkgatan 3 Boras Sweden
properties.description: Posted by TrekprincessAs good a place as any to start. This is where I live. I share a flat with my boyfriend. The picture is the view from our livingroom window, with the addition of my mother.

properties.name: Wigwam Hotel
properties.description: Posted by Trekprincess An absolute must for anyone traveling the mother road. A unique little hotel that is run by a very friendly man, the son of the man who built the wigwams. The rooms aren\'t very big but big enough and so full of charm. It\'s like staying in a piece of history.
